> The name tandoori is derived from tandoor, a type of brick and clay oven used throughout India that lends a distinctly smoky taste to everything from veggies and meat to naan bread. In this recipe, we've recreated the bold and pungent flavors with the help of a special Tandoori spice blend made with equal parts turmeric, cardamom, paprika, and coriander.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Trim and halve @eggplant{1} lengthwise, then slice each half into 1-inch wedges. Core, seed, and dice @red bell pepper{1} into ½-inch cubes. Halve, peel, and finely dice @shallot{1}. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Toss eggplant on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, 1/2 tsp @tandoori spice{1%tablespoon}, and a large pinch of @salt{1%pinch} and @pepper{1%pinch}. Roast ~{10-12%minutes}, turn, then finish roasting until soft and golden brown, another ~{10-12%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add peppers and shallots, and toss until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add ginger, garlic, and 1/2 tsp tandoori spice. Toss until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}.

Add @basmati rice{3/4%cup} and toss to coat. Add 1¾ cups @water{1.75%cups} and @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and bring to a boil. Reduce to a low simmer, and cover until tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

== Cilantro Yogurt Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{1}, half of the cilantro, and remaining 1/2 tsp tandoori spice. Season with salt and pepper, and thin to a drizzling consistency with 1 TBSP or so of @water{?1%tbsp}.

== To Serve ==

Serve roasted eggplant on a bed of rice. Drizzle with yogurt sauce, and finish with a sprinkle of cilantro and @pepitas{1%ounce}.